# Who Am I?

* Homebased preschool for 10 years in two states
* Certified teacher
* Taught in public schools
* Mom for 23 years
* Mother of 4 Eagle scouts

</br>

# We focus on


* Fine motor skills&mdash;practiced through cutting, gluing, drawing and writing.
* Cooperation, taking turns, sharing, sitting through story time (getting them Kindergarten ready).
* Learning letters through letter of the week, making letter books, a student letter teacher each week
* Wilsonâ€™s Fundations method of teaching phonics&mdash;how sounds work together to form words
* Learn numbers, sequencing, counting, math with manipulatives
* Science with labs
* Character counts&mdash;lessons on good character&mdash;good citizenship
* Fun monthly themes & colors
* Circle time with stories, songs, finger plays, calendar, weather, flag.

<br/>


# More Fun things we do

* Mystery can&mdash;student puts an item in the can and gives 3 clues and other students guess (they LOVE this),
* Beasley Bear&mdash;a bear that goes home with one student over the weekend and they draw or write about an event and report on their weekend to the class.
* Recess&mdash;outdoor (weather permitting) with Climbing structure, slide, steering wheel, Sand/water table
